latestPosts.caption:
It’s time. 

This collection is very close to my heart. It’s something I’ve been working on for the past year, deeply connected to my journey of moving back to Bombay. 

I often asked myself, what makes Bombay, Bombay? I found inspiration in the everyday—the streets, the architecture, the people, the traffic, the noise. My goal is to tap into the ordinary and overlooked, to encourage people to look at the mundane and familiar around us with a fresh perspective. 

We’ve used motifs that define the city and transformed them into pendants and rings. Each piece is unique and speaks to the ordinary things that make this city extraordinary.

So go ahead, be a tourist in your own city. Open your eyes and see that inspiration can be found all around you. 
This collection is inspired by the streets, made for you.

check it out on frostbitelab.com

latestPosts.caption:
Meet Shrikesh Choksi (@shrikeshchoksi), the visionary behind Frostbite Lab, a groundbreaking label fusing hip-hop swagger with traditional Indian techniques like meenakari and jadau. A lockdown dream sparked this unique journey, which Travel + Leisure India & South Asia explores in an exclusive interview. Discover how he went from initial outreach to collaborating with skilled artisans in Zaveri Bazaar, turning teeth into bold canvases for self-expression and carving out a new space for a loud, local, heritage-rooted luxury. Hear the story, see the sparkle: Swipe to explore Frostbite Lab’s fusion of hip-hop and heritage jewellry!

Interview by: Rooplekha Das

latestPosts.caption:
Last week was special; two separate features in magazines I’ve looked up to for a long, long time. 

Just as doing something that’s never been done will always come with challenges, reimagining Indian jewelry on Grillz was no exception…and both these interviews capture that story beautifully. 

A big thank you to @thewordmagazine and @thenodmag for sharing Frostbite with the world — this is only the beginning.

latestPosts.caption:
Another year, another DJ highlight post that no one asked for…

With over 150+ gigs this year, here are some of the top moments: 

1) Played for some dope brands - @dior @puma @capsulindia @marketplacebymainstreet @stampduty.in 

2) Spun with @keinemusikcrue and @fireboydml at Lake Como

3) Played for designers and companies I’ve always been inspired by - @zeptonow @all.things.wtf , @santanu_hazarika_art @kunalrawalofficial 

4) Did a B3B with the absolute 🐐s @djtennis @kahanimusic 

5) Worked with artists who’ve turned into fam - @lynston_blurryslur @nidadadj @kunalschhabra @mc_soopy @prithvidotpsd @yngprp @raemulla @adisaidthat @dishaan_ @tricksinghh @itstherealshai 

6) Party for @frostbite.lab launch (but more on that later) 

7) And of course, stayed regular at my favorite local venues - @sohohouse @slinkandbardot @neumaindia @cavos.experience @clubjolies 

S/o to the people that made it happen @partofmyniche @pracheemashru @vsumit @aneeshakotwani @jaymehta14 

2024 was blessed.

latestPosts.caption: Choksi is a Mumbai-based DJ and producer who’s made waves in LA, curating music for top venues and brands. At Soho House Mumbai, he blends his DJ sets with African percussion alongside Anand Bhagat. He’s also performed at NMACC, Neuma, and Olive, and collaborated with DIOR, Adidas, and Nike. Expect an eclectic mix of house, disco, retro, and Afro from his set! 🔥🪩🎵
